    39тЖТ## Default example
    41тЖТThe example below uses `tailwindcss` `@shadcn/ui` `tailwind-merge` `clsx`:
    42тЖТ
    43тЖТ```tsx
    44тЖТ'use client'
    45тЖТimport { OTPInput, SlotProps } from 'input-otp'
    46тЖТ<OTPInput
    47тЖТ  maxLength={6}
    48тЖТ  containerClassName="group flex items-center has-[:disabled]:opacity-30"
      тЖТтАж
   136тЖТ## How it works
   138тЖТThere's currently no native OTP/2FA/MFA input in HTML, which means people are either going with 1. a simple input design or 2. custom designs like this one.
   139тЖТThis library works by rendering an invisible input as a sibling of the slots, contained by a `relative`ly positioned parent (the container root called _OTPInput_).
   140тЖТ
   141тЖТ## Features
   143тЖТThis is the most complete OTP input on the web. It's fully featured 
   144тЖТ
   145тЖТ<details>
   146тЖТ<summary>Supports iOS + Android copy-paste-cut</summary>
   147тЖТ
   148тЖТhttps://github.com/guilhermerodz/input-otp/assets/10366880/bdbdc96a-23da-4e89-bff8-990e6a1c4c23
   149тЖТ
   150тЖТ</details>
      тЖТтАж
   198тЖТ### Auto tracks if the input has space in the right side for the badge
   200тЖТhttps://github.com/guilhermerodz/input-otp/assets/10366880/bf01af88-1f82-463e-adf4-54a737a92f59
   201тЖТ
   202тЖТ</details>
   203тЖТ
   204тЖТ## API Reference
   206тЖТ### OTPInput
   208тЖТThe root container. Define settings for the input via props. Then, use the `render` prop to create the slots.
   209тЖТ
   210тЖТ#### Props
   212тЖТ```ts
   213тЖТtype OTPInputProps = {
   214тЖТ  // The number of slots
   215тЖТ  maxLength: number
   216тЖТ
   217тЖТ  // Render function creating the slots
   218тЖТ  render: (props: RenderProps) => React.ReactElement
      тЖТтАж
